HEADWORD: Auf
<hw>Auf</hw> <pr>(⟦add⟧f)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>auph</ets>,
<ets>aulf</ets>, fr. Icel. <ets>⟦amac⟧lfr</ets> elf. See
<er>Elf</er>.]</ety> <altsp>[Also spelt <asp>oaf</asp>,
<asp>ouphe</asp>.]</altsp> <def>A changeling or elf child, -- that is,
one left by fairies; a deformed or foolish child; a simpleton; an
oaf.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Drayton.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Au fait</ent>⟦br⟧
